Gnathosoma . Rostrum extending beyond distal end of femur I (
Fig. 20
); palps 5 segmented, with one solenidion and two eupathidia distally; second palpal segments with two setae, fourth segment with one dorsal seta (
Fig. 19
).

Legs. Legs are rather short, about one third length of the idiosoma. The counts for the legs setae and solenidia (in parentheses): coxae 3 - 2 - 1 - 1 ; trochanters 1 - 1-2 - 1 ; femora 4 - 4 - 2 - 1 ; genua 3 - 3 - 1 -0; tibiae 4 - 4 - 2 - 2 ; tarsi 8 ( 1 ) - 8 ( 1 ) - 5 - 4 . Dorsal setae stouter and serrated (
Figs. 21–24
). Femur I with one dorsal seta leaf-like and another one minute and serrate and two ventral setae (
Fig. 21
). Tarsal claws hooked-like.
